=Description=

"Julie Cohen discusses a chapter from her forthcoming book, which explores the effects of expanding copyright, pervasive surveillance, and the increasingly opaque design of network architectures in the emerging networked information society.  The chapter argues that “access to knowledge” is a necessary but insufficient condition for human flourishing, and adds two additional conditions."
(http://cyber.law.harvard.edu/events/luncheon/2010/01/cohen)

